Yang had already gained admirers in the so-called Intellectual Dark Web for his focus on technological solutions for economic ills.
Yang’s campaign was built on his concern that increasing automation will eliminate jobs and drive Americans out of their economic and social spheres of life.
The idea of this mild-mannered software nerd dancing with stacks of hundred dollar bills on the “Yang Yacht” is so absurd that it is genuinely funny.
It is not as though Sean Hannity and Rush Limbaugh have hopped aboard the Yang Yacht.
Now, many of the same people are contrasting the old, slow, rusted Trump Train with the sleek, shiny, welcoming Yang Yacht.